The Federal High Court sitting in Makurdi yesterday sentenced one Otere Olafiku to two years imprisonment for possessing and altering $50 notes. The Makurdi zonal office of Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), Makurdi zonal had dragged the convict and two others to court on a two-count charge. At earlier proceedings of the court, the trio had pleaded not guilty But Olafiku later entered a plea bargaining with the Commission and changed not guilty to ‘guilty’. FULL TEXT: Father Kukah’s homily at funeral mass of… FG tasks professionals, engineers on effective… Oyo Assembly begins Amotekun bill consideration Thursday Kogi guber: Court to deliver judgement on authentic PDP… ALSO READ: Expert calls for more actions, funding to contain spread of Lassa fever As a result of his guilty plea, and subsequent review of the facts of the case, the prosecution counsel, Y.Y Tarfa, prayed the court to convict him accordingly. However, counsel to the convict I. M Mari, pleaded with the Court to temper justice with mercy, saying his client was a first-time offender. Delivering the judgement, Justice Mobolaji Olajuwon sentenced the convict to two years imprisonment, with an option of fine of One Hundred Thousand Naira (N100,000.00). SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.